caption: I really loved the skinned chicken with coconut rice and clear broth here. The waitress was very polite and nice. 10/10 recommend the food. I wish I knew where they buy their chicken from and how they prepare it. I rarely happen to like the chicken taste and this was definitely exceptional.
Dont buy wine here! They loot you by selling 7$ wine bottle for 35$. Just Ridiculous.....

I feel bad writing a bad review but I feel like this is what the food I got deserves. One of the dishes literally has 5 chunk of potatoes and one chunk of tomato in some gravy sauce. Maybe 3 pieces of onions and stuff, nothing else ( I think this is Kentang Gulai Kurma). I feel like the restaurant put in whatever cheap ingredients into the dishes and call it a meal. The other dish is some street noodle and 90% of it is just... noodles. I really don't think the food is nearly worth the price.  I can't even imagine eating this again for a dinner even if someone pays me! :/
Exceptional takeout service & great Malaysian, Singaporean & Indonesian food — thank you!
This place has amazing Singaporean street food. The options are plenty and all of what we tried so far has been excellent
Mediocre taste and portion size is way too small for the price. Regular dishes like a red curry costs $24 with no extraordinary ingredients. I am never going to eat at this place again.

The dishes in the food flavor wise is not that bad at all and it tastes very good but the amount of food you get for the price you pay is not great as it's very expensive. Be wary on getting the beef cheek as it's not a lot.  It taste very good but very pricey for how much you get.  Again, nothing against the food as everything tasted great!  It's just the amount of food that you get it's not a lot for the price paid.

WHAT AN EXCEPTIONAL EXPERIENCE!!! I went to this restaurant in my attempts to explore Malaysian food scene of Boston. This restaurant is somewhat new, so I thought that I would try it out. Boy, I'm glad I did because it was one of the best meals I've had in a long time. I was born in Cambodia and the moment I step foot into the restaurant, it reminds me immediately of sitting in a Cambodian restaurant in the middle of Phnom Penh. The servers were courteous and extremely helpful with the extensive menu. They have a street food menu that composts of noodles and rice dishes. I wanted to specifically try the nasi lamak and noodle in curry sauce. Unfortunately, they didn't have anymore nasi lamak, but the substitute Hainese chicken dish was a great sub for it. The noodle dish was delicious. Noodle was soft but not mushy. The curry broth that the noodle sits in was thick and super flavorful! it was creamy and pack full of nostalgic aromas. The combo of land meat and seafood is a classic for Southeast Asian food, so I'm glad they stuck with it. The Hainese chicken, though not the best i've had, was a strong contender. The chicken was tender, juicy, and heavily seasoned. That's what chicken needs is to be heavily seasoned. The dipping sauce was fragrant and pack a punch. The soup that accompanies the rice dish is mild yet refreshing, a perfect and classic partner for SouthEast version of rice and meat.  We also got the fried red snapper and 3 flavor sauce. The fish was fried to perfection. Yes, it is the whole entire fish. It was crispy and crunchy and crackily and just pure awesome. Really stroke my Asian-ness. Yes, the head comes on it too. The sauce that comes on top of the fish is AMAZING!!!! ton of fish sauce aka natural MSG aka umami bomb aka the shindig. Their entree really made to be eaten with jasmine rice which are sold by person and not by portion. You pay $2 for unlimited jasmine rice. They come to your table in a shiny round vessels which brings me back to Cambodia. Just classic.  The scallops appetizer seems pricey but well worth the price for the single bite. The scallops are seared resulting in a dark, caramelized flavor, then the shredded duck along with the fish sauce base sauce compliments the delicate flavor of the scallops. topped off with some refreshing sliced scallion. YUM!  Lastly, roasted duck salad. Nothing to laugh about. The duck was tender and flavorful. The rest of the salad is pretty classic Southeast Asian salad consisting of hearty crunchy cabbage and herbs. The dressing is sweet with the a strong salt that really brings out the brightness of the duck. While the dressing is strong, the duck is still the star flavor of the dish.  Overall, I would recommend this restaurant if you're an adventurous eater and veterans of Vietnamese food. They have a combination of Southeast Asia - Vietnamese, Khmer, Thai, Chinese flavors. Not too punchy but just enough to leave wanting more and more. Looking forward to going back soon.
A small place with really good pho.  Doesn't have all the msg and sugar that typical pho places have. My boys and I love coming here after soccer practice.

Indonesian food is a rarity in the Boston area.  There is also a good selection of Singapore dishes including a menu of hawker favorites like chicken rice and laksa and Indonesian staples like Nasi and Mi Goreng.
Delicious south east asian food with a separate vegetarian menu too. They even have SE Asian beers.
Great food with great quality and quantity. Would go again for some Asian food.
This spot never disappoints. They have good food for convenient prices, there is no waiting time even when the place is loaded.
Their Roti is delicious and buttery. So rich it reminds me of Yorkshire pudding.
The best place to get Asian food in the Boston area! Would highly recommend!
So many options and sooooo delicious! Get the pork belly appetizer!
The food is amazing, really nice cozy place, good service, really recommend
Wish it was closer to my house, I would come every week.

Food I decided to come here because of the great ratings in Yelp, but I was disappointed. The food was very mediocre. The highlight was the scallop appetiser, but still not perfect. The chicken betel leaf was interesting, but I didn’t realise it was a cold dish. The steam snapper dumplings were okay as well. For main course, I had the crispy whole fish and it was so sweet that I couldn’t finish half of it. The red duck curry was not bad. Finally, the desserts. Both of us had black sticky rice. Not a fan.  Everything else The decor was nice, but a bit too dark for my taste. I don’t think the restaurant is doing very well. We came here on a Friday night and there were only four tables, and there were not many takeouts. I definitely will not come back and don’t recommend it to anyone.
Found this nugget tucked away on Mass Ave. The chicken on betel leaf was fantastic. As was the dessert of banana ice cream with cinnamon

Good place. My husband and I got the pork belly appetizer to share. It was strictly okay. Deep fried, and seemed unhealthy. We ordered the duck red curry and singapore beef as the main course. The red curry was phenomenal. Had a nice spicy flavor and extremely tasty. The singapore beef was good as well. It's a family dining place with a vast menu. Could use a little work on the ambience. The place smelled of fish a little bit.
this place does it for me. will surely make a return trip. food is similar to a cafe in portland i loved.
Very good food, albeit a bit pricy for what it is. Lovely atmosphere, but I think the alcohol choices are a bit wine-heavy and could fit the menu a bit better.

Amazing food prepared with dedication and love for detail. We ordered the gado-gado salad which was a great mix of peanut taste, coconut milk and greens, and as a main the aceh chicken and the red duck - the flavours were so rich and the mix of vegetables and fruits just crazy good. The combination with litchi and apple eggplant was just heavenly. We'll definitely come again!
Interesting and innovative Asian eats
Great food! Restaurant practicing great social distancing and outdoor dining practices. Vegetarian menu A+!

Wow. Unbelievable flavors, presentation and service. This place hits all the delicious South Asian flavors (lemongrass, Thai basil, curries) but without being too sweet. Can’t recommend Chalawan enough!

Food is not good; I am not sure where the high ratings come from. Taste and quality are not there. This place definitely does not worth even half of the prices they charge. Roti was poorly made and did not taste fresh at all. Chicken skin starter has whole pieces of fried chicken skins of sizes larger than your hand which was really unappealing; The eggplant relish was good though. Salmon salad with watermelon was simply a bad idea because they do not go well together. Watermelon and cucumber in the salad were old. The salmon is not fresh and overcooked. The dressing also did not taste good. Asian greens side was too salty.

Do yourself a favor and check out Chalawan. I’ve been 3 times, and there are enough dishes that you can try something new every time. And literally everything I’ve tried has been amazing. HIGHLY recommend the salmon and watermelon salad. And anything with soft shell crab! Oh, and the roti is the best you will find. Service is always incredible, staff is so nice. Will def be back again!
Food is delicious and the staff is incredibly friendly and helpful. Can't wait to come back!

two days ago was our first time we visited this place. But It is no doubt not the last time. We passed a splendid evening with the efficient service, with the great  food and booze and with the friendly charge. We will surely visit there soon.

I got takeout from here tonight and the pickup was very clean/sanitary and professional. I got the dumplings, the softshell crab and the pork hock and it was all very delicious!! The dumplings were AMAZING - really unique flavor, sweet, herbacious, light, and aromatic - I will 100% be ordering them again. The crab was simply delicious - very fresh tasting and excellently prepared with that crispy crunch I crave and the sauce paired with it perfectly too. The pork was succulent and juicy with a crackling skin and came with lettuce and sauces to wrap bite-size pieces up in. It was all very good and I can't wait to come back and share with friends.
Food is simply amazing!
Was not thrilled
This place is an all in one stop for Asian cuisine. They are experts in Thai, Malaysian and Vietnamese food, and the menu is conveniently designed to show the different categories.

This is a nice Asian  hole in the wall Thai/Fusion restaurant. Their food is flavorful, and reasonably priced, especially for Boston . They do offer a free Thai Iced Tea if you check in, so make sure to do so!

I came here on a Saturday for brunch around noon. With such a high rating on yelp I was surprised how empty it was. The service was great but I was hesitant on their menu items as the place was so empty. I was super hungry so decided to order a lot of food. Between two of us we ordered two entrees and two soups.
Excellent food and service. You would have to travel to Asia to get better food nothing like this place on this caliber  in the Boston area. P.S. if you are vegatarian ask for the vegatarian  menu.
Amazing new spot. The betel leaf starter is really good. Great menu and very friendly staff.

We were not impressed. The dishes sound intriguing but the taste was not there. There are lots of other better Asian restaurants around Cambridge area. Fish dumplings were soggy and uninteresting. Maybe restaurant will improve as time goes on.
Spice delights
Great food - exciting menu. Loved the duck curry. The calamari appetizer was delish. Great service as well. Can't wait to go back.
This place is AMAZING. The people who work there are so sweet, the food is incredible and unique, they have a vegetarian menu, and it’s not that expensive for a very nice dining experience.

One of the most flavorful meals I’ve ever had. All the dishes that we ordered are so well balanced, presented well and are unique from the “regular” southeast Asian cuisine. Highly recommend the chicken betel leaf, steamed snapper dumplings, Singaporean beef and all the curries! The staff was awesome and brought out a surprise Thai tea custard and coffee ice cream for my mom’s birthday celebrations! Would go back in a heartbeat :)
So dang good. Pork belly. Yes. All the other foods. Yes as well.
Great service, great food and great staff. Highly recommend.
I recommend the snapper with the malbec! However, the best part was the Thai tea caramel custard w/ ice cream!!!
The best

After hearing so many good thing about Chalawan restaurant, I finally decided to give it a try! I was surprised by the quality of the dishes! Excellent Indonesian food! We tried both chicken ($20) and beef ($30) and they were so yummy! You pay $2 for rice and they keep refilling your plate! The decorations, plates and even the water jars were so authentic and elegant! For desert I tried cream brûlée with almond ice cream ($8) and it was just as good as the food! I didn’t try the starters or sides, but they sounds delicious! Nice place to dine with family and friends. Also super friendly staff. Will definitely go back there soon. (I heard other tables complement about the food and service constantly 😊)
There's a separate vegetarian menu that you have to ask for. I had the red curry which was good. The Thai Tea custard is also recommended.
Wow! Awesome food

The food was excellent. There are tonnes of vegetarian options as well (they have a separate vegetarian menu too). The pork belly starter is extremely well cooked and delicious. The Bornean Adam Tahu comes highly recommended: it is the right amount of sweet and spicy.  The dessert selection is pretty good too: we had the banana cake with coconut ice cream and we could have had 20 of those. There are a few beer options (besides Singha) and a rather extensive wine collection. The decor is stunning: the mural is very eye catching of course, but there are a lot of quirky little details (like the tiffin boxes on the wall and the newspaper wallpaper in the bathroom). If you want to bring a large group, make sure you book well in advance and the place is pretty cozy.
Turmeric

Really good food and service. Their betel leaf appetizer (either chicken or tofu) is a must try. They have a separate vegetarian menu for non-vegetarian customers. They serve unlimited rice separately with their entree options.
Beautiful restaurant. Small and intimate. Delicious and interesting food. Lovely service. A bit more expensive but worth it.

Dinner tonight at Chalawan was one of the most enjoyable meals I've had in Cambridge. The flavors were amazing. We shared seven dishes, and each was unique and delightful, with beautiful presentation. The service was perfectly attentive, with neither lapses nor interruptions. Importantly, the atmosphere was comfortable; even with a packed house, the restaurant was quiet enough that we were able to converse without having to raise our voices. I can't wait to go back to try more from the menu.
Amazing vegetarian menu
Seared Alaska Scallops Steamed Snapper Dumpling Anything from the entrees Enjoy!
Great service, great food. Perfect spot for a date.

Fried soft shell crab tasted good, but used low quality frozen crab. Curry duck was flavorful, but half bowl was just fat with skin. Pork belly was not well marinated, flavorful on the outside yet bland inside. Pricy with the portions and qualities. Friendly service and very crowed, but don’t think worthy.

I want to say "don't go, it's terrible," because I'm terrified of how popular this place is going to become and I plan to frequent it often. I can't do that though, this place is special. From the moment we walked in I suspected I was going to love everything about the place and it still exceeded my expectations by a large margin. It's hard to overstate just how good the food is and the service was phenomenal. Already looking forward to going back.
Great service! Food was very tasty also!
Delicious! Had the fish dumplings and fish curry and both were great. also had creme brulee for dessert which was amazing. Will definitely go back!
Went here for dinner and everything was outstanding. We got wine, fish curry and the duck. Everything was so good and filling. We will definitely come back
Amazing food, authentic, great service. What else can you wish for.

We made a great decision to come here for a casual birthday dinner. We were later than our reservation and the staff were so nice and served so fast. At the end they even sang the birthday song. Highly recommended.
Stopped in here on a whim—best decision! Excellent food, excellent service, and lovely atmosphere. 100% recommend

The food here is incredible. I had the duck red curry and the creme brulee; both exceeded my expectations, and there were rave reviews all around the table with my 6 person group. The service was also great; the water cups were small but always refilled. I have one problem: the difficulty of reading the menu. Written entirely in italicized font, there are no commas, no list offset thus giving the impression of a large block of text, and no punctuation. No commas between ingredients! Plus, the lighting was dim and the table could have benefitted even from some candles. I'm young, in my 20s. Back in the day I scored an 800 in critical reading on the SAT. I'm sorry, this may be the pettiest comment I've ever made on Google maps, but reading the menu shouldn't be a chore. I would still return.
There is a lot of art to buy and look at and there food is pretty good but there very slow

Terrific finely rendered dishes in a pleasant venue. Nice to have the chance to mix and match various SE Asian cuisines, all focused through the artistry of a talented kitchen. Although this is a not a low-budget choice along a (happily rejuvenated) stretch of good options, it may be among the best of them. 4 of us enjoyed 3 appetizers, 4 main dishes, a delicious take on banana bread, a fine Vietnamese coffee, and a bottle of wine for $176 including tip. I'd advocate for a broader beer selection (though I don't drink beer much), and some by the glass wine selection. Tidy portions, richly flavored. We'll be back!
Great food. Unique menu with complex flavors. Great service. Will definitely be back.
Really great food and nonalcoholic drinks

This is a wonderful new restaurant on Mass Ave near Porter square. My husband and I were looking for a place to eat last night and we were invited into restaurant by two of their staff members who told us about their 'soft opening'. So glad we gave them a try. The service was beyond excellent, the atmosphere was great and food was delicious. The chef supposedly was really famous in Bali and moved here to open up a restaurant. The menu is unique and everything we tried was so flavorful. We got a free starter, scallops that were so so good. We then ordered two types is curry, one duck, one lamb and both were amazing. For desert we had coconut ice cream and a pudding. Thank you Chalawan for a great dinner, we will be back!! So excited about this new Asian restaurant in our neighborhood, just what was missing.
